707956f-a.title: Manhattan: 2nd Avenue - 99th Street (East)
707956f-a.text:
Second Avenue, north from East 99th Street, as photographed
from the uptown ''El'' platform.
View 2 is from the northern extremity of this station and is
closer to 100th Street.
Note the occupancy of all three tracks, includ'ng the express
line in the center.
June 7, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

714925f-a.title: Manhattan: 99th Street (East) - 2nd Avenue
714925f-a.text:
East 99th Street, south side, west from (224) but not including Second
Ave. Elevated. line shown is the Third Ave.

714926f.title: Manhattan: 99th Street (East) - 2nd Avenue
714926f.text:
East 99th Street, north side, east from (No. 211) but not including
Third to and including Second Aves. (Second Ave. Elevated Line at the latter
point). Shown at the left are portions of P.S. No. 109 which occupies
building lot Nos. 213 to 219.
July 14, 1936.
